BBC Awards for Wold Music, 2008 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio3/worldmusic/a4wm2008/2008_tinariwen_album.shtml&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio3/worldmusic/a4wm2008/2008_tinariwen_album.shtml&lt;/a&gt;

Some have called them the Rolling Stones of the Sahara. Don't give so much credit to those decrepit colonialists. The RS can only wish. Tinariwen is the real deal. They are rebels - kalazhnikov in one hand, electric guitar in the other. This is rebel music. When opressed people sing they always deliver their souls.

Enjoy this terrorist album. It will bomb the shit out of your preconceived notions.

May the lord, the Flying Spaghetti Monster, bless their music.
Ramen!

